One person has been reportedly shot dead as rival cult groups clashed on Thursday night in Sapele, Delta State. Details of the clash is not clear as of the time of this report. However, DAILY POST reports that the indigenes and residents are now living in fear following the incessant killings by cult groups in the town. When contacted for confirmation of the report on Friday morning, the Delta State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe said, “I will find out please.”